@Sjonnie2nd Because [the lack of support for ESM modules in the pkg builder](https://github.com/vercel/pkg/issues/1291) is not an Axios issue and no fixes are required in the project. Starting from v1.x, Axios moved to ESM modules. 
Although the package is distributed with a prebuilt `commonjs` module version, the loader must support conditional export in order to load it automatically, otherwise, you must take care of importing the correct module type yourself.
So for legacy packers use explicit import with `require`

```js
const axios = require('axios/dist/node/axios.cjs');
```

