> In your test file the `import getPhotosByAlbumId from '../index.js'` points to a module which imports`axios`. In ESM all imports are evaluated first, this applies to the `axios` import in `index.js` files. After module is evaluated, the `jest.mock` call has no effect on it. To make this work: in your test file should import `getPhotosByAlbumId` dynamically after mocking `axios`.
> 
> Another problem are default exports. You should adjust your mock and imports like this:
> 
> ```ts
> jest.unstable_mockModule("axios", () => ({
>   default: jest.fn(),
> }));
> 
> const { default: axios } = await import("axios");
> const { default: getPhotosByAlbumId } = await import("../index.js");
> ```

