This is expected and it's part of the work involved in bumping across major versions. [It's expected that you'll have breaks like this when you do a major version change](https://semver.org/). 

In this particular case, it's because version `v0.27.2` was using [Node's deprecated](https://nodejs.org/api/url.html#urlparseurlstring-parsequerystring-slashesdenotehost) `url.parse` and `v1.4.0` is using URL ([see the MDN docs](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL)).

They have different parse logic. This isn't specific to Axios. This is an upstream difference.

```
> const url = require("url");
> let user = "user"; let password = "12345!@";
> let location = `http://${user}:${encodeURIComponent(password)}@localhost:8080`;
> let oldWay = url.parse(location);
> let newWay = new URL(location);
> console.log(oldWay.auth)
user:12345!@
> console.log(newWay.password)
12345!%40
```

