Interceptors are part of Axios core, but the final installation of headers based on the payload, specific to the platform, is done by the adapter immediately before sending the request, which is quite logical. Axios core should not know anything about Node. js-specific implementations and somehow use them outside the adapter, since this violates the components' area of responsibility and will also lead to dead code ending up on the browser platform. It’s hard to imagine why you needed to manually install this header and be able to get it inside the interceptor. Maybe you should change directly the FormData payload inside the interceptor as a workaround...
In addition, you can use the native implementation of FormData in node18, where Axios supports a custom boundary header, but again, it’s hard for me to imagine any practical need for this.

